        <num>CC 1249</num>
        <heading>1249.  Wages for services to ascendant</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1249.  Wages for services to ascendant.
The obligation of collation does not exclude the child or descendant coming to the succession of his father, mother or other ascendant, from claiming wages which may be due to him for having administered the property of the ascendant, or for other services.</p>
        </content>
